if i ran the same amount of volume to it, assuming the conversion metrics stayed the same, i'd be making $20k per day lmao

the only difference between making $1.5k & $20k a day was the niche & the lander i drove traffic to

There's a lot of BS in the AI space. Lot of hoopla and over-complication by non-software engineers to try and bully you into buying their course. 

Forget that noise. If you want to make money with AI on the side, there's only 5 things you need to know.

- which models work best for which tasks
- cost/benefit analysis across models
- when to start new chats vs rely on existing context
- how to get consistent output formats for a workflow (this is the basis of automation)
- how to string together models (output as input, which is the basis of agents)

